<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idb52e2bc4-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d" identifier="/us/usc/t6/s541"><num value="541">§ 541.</num><heading> Definitions</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">For purposes of this subchapter:</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idb52e2bc5-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d" identifier="/us/usc/t6/s541/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> The term “agency” includes any entity, organizational unit, program, or function.</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idb52e2bc6-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d" identifier="/us/usc/t6/s541/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> The term “transition period” means the 12-month period beginning on the effective date of this chapter.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="idb52e2bc7-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d">(<ref href="/us/pl/107/296/tXV/s1501">Pub. L. 107–296, title XV, § 1501</ref>, <date date="2002-11-25">Nov. 25, 2002</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/116/2307">116 Stat. 2307</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idb52e2bc8-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idb52e2bc9-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I75" topic="referencesInText" id="idb52e2bca-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d">
<heading class="centered smallCaps">References in Text</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">The effective date of this chapter, referred to in par. (2), is 60 days after <date date="2002-11-25">Nov. 25, 2002</date>, see <ref href="/us/pl/107/296/s4">section 4 of Pub. L. 107–296</ref>, set out as an Effective Date note under <ref href="/us/usc/t6/s101">section 101 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
